div.div: Store best queries in a database

switch.text: Store best queries in a database

div.div:
Manager requests Builder
to create queryable groups
and initializes all handlers
required for fuzzing
The initial population is created by generating queries for every entity set separately.
Selector selects a pair of queries or a random entity set according to the fitness score of the population

When the score of newly generated queries is worse than an average fitness score of the population, the queries are not stored in the database. Offspring queries which have worse score than their parents are trimmed as well.
When a database connection is established, the fuzzing process starts
